This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with point cloud analysis, which is a common problem in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a convolutional neural network architecture for this task, which is a popular technique in computer vision. 

The paper also involves learning from relations and geometric topology constraints, which suggests it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of geometric priors and spatial layout of points suggests that the paper could also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks suggests that the paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
